    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>My Grandma sometimes forgets the date and day of the week as she gets older. She doesn't use a smartphone, only analogue clocks. She doesn't know English, so digital clocks wouldn't help. Some digital clocks also lose their time and date after a power cycle. I couldn't get her a voice assistant, as Google doesn't support the Vietnamese language yet. Since there was nothing available for her, I decided to hack together a solution.</p>\n<p>I soldered together a <a href=\"https://www.raspberrypi.com/products/raspberry-pi-zero-w/\">Raspberry Pi W</a> and an <a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/2097\">Adafruit PiTFT display</a>. The Pi W was used on my Prusa MK3S Printer to run OctoPrint, but the performance was so bad <a href=\"https://github.com/guysoft/OctoPi/issues/318#issuecomment-284762963\">it's no longer recommended</a>. The Adafruit Display was used as a touchscreen for <a href=\"https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1601055\">OctoPrint's Touch UI</a>, but I found it easier to use my phone than the interface. The Pi W's GPIO pins connect directly to the Adafruit display.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/b064b/solder-01.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"solder 01\"\n        title=\"solder 01\"\n        src=\"/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/8a34a/solder-01.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/08b27/solder-01.jpg 213w,\n/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/6f6b2/solder-01.jpg 425w,\n/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/8a34a/solder-01.jpg 850w,\n/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/63107/solder-01.jpg 1275w,\n/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/fef31/solder-01.jpg 1700w,\n/static/bb00c430bdad5f5d7e853cf01ec93c6e/b064b/solder-01.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/81f49/solder-02.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.11737089201877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"solder 02\"\n        title=\"solder 02\"\n        src=\"/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/8a34a/solder-02.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/08b27/solder-02.jpg 213w,\n/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/6f6b2/solder-02.jpg 425w,\n/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/8a34a/solder-02.jpg 850w,\n/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/63107/solder-02.jpg 1275w,\n/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/fef31/solder-02.jpg 1700w,\n/static/6e74251174f1863f5d6baa434153cb58/81f49/solder-02.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/81f49/solder-03.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.11737089201877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"solder 03\"\n        title=\"solder 03\"\n        src=\"/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/8a34a/solder-03.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/08b27/solder-03.jpg 213w,\n/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/6f6b2/solder-03.jpg 425w,\n/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/8a34a/solder-03.jpg 850w,\n/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/63107/solder-03.jpg 1275w,\n/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/fef31/solder-03.jpg 1700w,\n/static/65c478c995e25a4a4c60e1ba802fdf42/81f49/solder-03.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Adafruit provides <a href=\"https://github.com/adafruit/Raspberry-Pi-Installer-Scripts\">scripts on their GitHub</a> to install drivers for their displays, HATs and add-ons.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell-session\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-shell-session line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-shell-session\"><span class=\"token command\"><span class=\"token shell-symbol important\">$</span> <span class=\"token bash language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> python3 adafruit-pitft.py --display<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>35r --rotation<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">270</span> --install-type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>console</span></span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>I wrote a simple Python script that would output the day of the week, the date, and the time. It was difficult to change the font size on the terminal, so I used a package called <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/art/\">art</a> to display large ASCII art which filled up the display. The source code can be found on my GitHub at <a href=\"https://github.com/calvinbui/pi-clock\">calvinbui/pi-clock</a>. The package did not support the Vietnamese alphabet, so I had to remove their <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diacritic\">diacritics</a>. To autostart the Python script, I edited <code class=\"language-text\">/etc/rc.local</code> and added <code class=\"language-text\">/home/pi/pi-clock/main.py > /dev/tty1</code> before the <code class=\"language-text\">exit 0</code>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 824px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/931746e88cafc30a6f98c7de81891bcf/a0e79/python.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.441314553990615%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"python\"\n        title=\"python\"\n        src=\"/static/931746e88cafc30a6f98c7de81891bcf/a0e79/python.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/931746e88cafc30a6f98c7de81891bcf/53f68/python.png 213w,\n/static/931746e88cafc30a6f98c7de81891bcf/df70d/python.png 425w,\n/static/931746e88cafc30a6f98c7de81891bcf/a0e79/python.png 824w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 824px) 100vw, 824px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The clock now hangs in her cabinet next to where she sits to watch television. It is powered using a single micro-USB cable, which automatically turns it on whenever it is plugged in. The Python script autostarts after boot. The Pi W is also connected to the Internet, so it will always have the correct time synced.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/81f49/clock-01.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.11737089201877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"clock 01\"\n        title=\"clock 01\"\n        src=\"/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/8a34a/clock-01.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/08b27/clock-01.jpg 213w,\n/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/6f6b2/clock-01.jpg 425w,\n/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/8a34a/clock-01.jpg 850w,\n/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/63107/clock-01.jpg 1275w,\n/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/fef31/clock-01.jpg 1700w,\n/static/05caeb8249caf91ba865ab71b908bc0f/81f49/clock-01.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/81f49/clock-02.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.11737089201877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"clock 02\"\n        title=\"clock 02\"\n        src=\"/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/8a34a/clock-02.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/08b27/clock-02.jpg 213w,\n/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/6f6b2/clock-02.jpg 425w,\n/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/8a34a/clock-02.jpg 850w,\n/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/63107/clock-02.jpg 1275w,\n/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/fef31/clock-02.jpg 1700w,\n/static/b6428d98b4844a008e9bff7eca34cec5/81f49/clock-02.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"My Grandma sometimes forgets the date and day of the week as she gets older. She doesn't use a sma